stories.text:
We use CircleCI at our company, but I've been pretty frustrated with their uptime, issues with jobs being triggered, VMs not being allocated, etc. We have a compact test suite that runs on every branch with an open github PR, and it's really disruptive to the organization's productivity when there's a CircleCI outage. It effectively blocks our developers from making progress (or at least merging code).

I realize CI is a complicated thing to build, but I'm wondering: are there better alternatives out there that we should try? What have your experiences been with CircleCI or other tools?
